00:17:19,882 --> 00:17:25,246
moment, and we are doing that and not arguing inside the

265
00:17:25,286 --> 00:17:27,427
team that should we do premium or free-to-play.

266
00:17:29,618 --> 00:17:32,819
Also, very interesting stuff happened to design process.

267
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:38,901
When we started the project, we had a quite small team at that

268
00:17:38,981 --> 00:17:43,663
time, about 15 people, and I was the only designer.

269
00:17:44,683 --> 00:17:45,443
Big mistake.

270
00:17:46,642 --> 00:17:50,984
And also, the process was quite like a waterfall.

271
00:17:51,844 --> 00:17:55,485
So during a sprint, I did some design.

272
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:57,866
Artists did the assets.

273
00:17:58,146 --> 00:17:59,366
We implemented it.

274
00:18:00,187 --> 00:18:01,907
And surprise, it failed.

275
00:18:02,647 --> 00:18:04,048
And we just lost two weeks.

276
00:18:04,128 --> 00:18:06,509
And then we did that again, and it failed again.

277
00:18:07,289 --> 00:18:11,490
So we realized that we are not agile enough, and also that

278
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:15,031
one designer can't solve all that stuff.

279
00:18:16,052 --> 00:18:20,434
So we totally changed our team culture that, hey, everybody's

280
00:18:20,494 --> 00:18:21,554
a game designer.

281
00:18:22,255 --> 00:18:24,335
Everybody is free to contribute.

282
00:18:24,876 --> 00:18:27,837
Anybody can, anytime, say that this sucks.

283
00:18:28,317 --> 00:18:29,757
We are not happy with this.

284
00:18:30,178 --> 00:18:31,838
So it's very frank culture.

285
00:18:32,358 --> 00:18:35,600
And then we changed it so that, hey, let's have always a very

286
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:39,021
big kickoff meeting where everybody in the team is

287
00:18:39,716 --> 00:18:41,838
who is working on that particular feature,

288
00:18:42,298 --> 00:18:45,881
let's talk about design true together so that everybody's happy.

289
00:18:46,162 --> 00:18:50,205
