290
00:18:50,566 --> 00:18:52,347
And then when we start to implement,

291
00:18:53,428 --> 00:18:56,250
all the time we kind of double check the design.

292
00:18:56,791 --> 00:19:01,195
If there are any flaws, on the fly we change the design.

293
00:19:01,775 --> 00:19:04,538
So we can already in the mockups,

294
00:19:04,998 --> 00:19:06,519
for example, see that, hey, UIs...

295
00:19:07,969 --> 00:19:11,770
they can't handle the information, let's simplify.

296
00:19:12,530 --> 00:19:16,311
Or when we have implemented the very first version, we can see that

297
00:19:16,911 --> 00:19:21,413
oh, the design doesn't work, it's not perfect, let's quickly iterate it.

298
00:19:22,093 --> 00:19:24,453
And that was a simple thing that we changed

299
00:19:25,234 --> 00:19:28,995
and it kind of improved our productivity a lot.

300
00:19:29,315 --> 00:19:31,035
And it also kind of kept the...

301
00:19:31,715 --> 00:19:34,877
Kind of the team morale went up, because everybody felt that,

302
00:19:34,897 --> 00:19:38,518
hey, we all are responsible that this is a great game,

303
00:19:38,558 --> 00:19:39,558
and this is a fun game.

304
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:48,542
Then, next big learning for me was user testing.

305
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:55,105
I know that we all are, we are big artists.

306
00:19:55,955 --> 00:20:03,062
We kind of want to nurture our babies and we don't want to show it anyone before it's perfect.

307
00:20:03,723 --> 00:20:04,964
So let's hide it.

308
00:20:06,706 --> 00:20:08,047
And that's totally stupid.

309
00:20:08,067 --> 00:20:08,107
So...

310
00:20:13,111 --> 00:20:17,175
You know that how blind we will be soon when we are developing a game.

311
00:20:17,355 --> 00:20:20,138
We are doing the same thing week after week,

312
00:20:20,538 --> 00:20:23,862
and then the team starts to argue that is this good enough,

313
00:20:24,002 --> 00:20:27,425
is this fun, or is this not, and it's so subjective.

